definition.value: An organic anion that is the conjugate base of methanol.
An organic anion that is the conjugate base of ethanol.
A morpholine N-oxide resulting from the oxidation of the amino group of N-methylmorpholine.
An acid in which an acidic -OH  group has been replaced by an -OOH  group.
An organic monosodium salt that has ethoxide as the counterion.
An indole compound having a 2-(dimethylamino)ethyl group at the 3-position and a (pyrrolidin-1-ylsulfonyl)methyl group at the 5-position.
An organic sodium salt having 4-[3,6-bis(diethylamino)xanthenium-9-yl]benzene-1,3-disulfonate as the counterion.
A cell permeable inhibitor for caspase proteases.
4-Aminobenzoic acid in which one of the hydrogens attached to the nitrogen is substituted by a butyl group.

An aza-steroid that is inasteride in which the tert-butyl group is replaced by a 2,5-bis(trifluoromethyl)phenyl group. A synthetic 4-azasteroid, dutasteride is a selective inhibitor of both the type 1 and type 2 isoforms of steroid 5alpha-reductase, an intracellular enzyme that converts testosterone to 5alpha-dihydrotestosterone. Dutasteride is used for the treatment of symptomatic benign prostatic hyperplasia in men with an enlarged prostate gland.
An organic dilithium salt having 6-amino-2-[(hydrazinocarbonyl)amino]-1,3-dioxo-2,3-dihydro-1H-benzo[de]isoquinoline-5,8-disulfonate as the counterion.
A cardenolide glycoside consisting of digitoxigenin having a beta-D-glucopyrananosyl-(1->4)-alpha-L-acofriopyranosyl moiety attached at the 3-position.
A benzofuropyranochromene that is 3H,7H-[1]benzofuro[3,2-c]pyrano[3,2-g]chromene substituted at positions 7a and 10 by hydroxy groups and at position 3 by a gem-dimethyl group.
An acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of any steroidal carboxylic acid.
